cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on evaluating and analyzing the performance of wireless routing protocols in different network loads and varying number of nodes. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the impact of changing routing strategies on the performance of the protocols, which can be related to information theory. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper does not directly discuss security, but the evaluation of routing protocols can have implications for network security. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the performance trade-offs of the protocols, which can be related to distributed computing. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the scalability of the protocols in denser networks, which can be related to social and information networks.
